race.comment: AMANOAH (8) in her first run for the new stable she resumed with a gritty on-pace victory over 1460m at Queanbeyan. Sure, to have improved further and Ramsbotham retains the ride from the good barrier. Confidence is high and sure to be thereabouts. COMPLAISANCE (7) big improver at her second run back when taking control early before being nailed on the line when second over 1200m at Nowra. Set to peak today and can take up a position from the sticky gate. Each way. HIP HIP OLE (10) unwanted in betting at her second race start when taken to the front for a dominant 3 len victory over 1400m at Wagga. Senior rider goes on and can figure prominently again. ROTHO BRO (6) no match for Zocketman at his second run back when an encouraging third over 1150m at Beaumont (Newcastle). This looks more to his liking and will relish the extra ground.
